org.jcvi.jillion.sam.header

Interface SamReadGroup


  • public interface SamReadGroup
    SamReadGroup is a way to group reads as belonging to a particular set. Often Read Groups are used to note which reads came from which sequencing run or pool.
    Author:
    dkatzel

        The predicted median insert size.

      • getId

        String getId()
        Get the unique ID. The value of ID is used in the ReservedSamAttributeKeys.READ_GROUP tag.
        Returns:
        a String; will never be null.

      • getPlatformUnit

        String getPlatformUnit()
        Get the unique Platform unit (e.g. flowcell-barcode.lane for Illumina or slide for SOLiD).
        Returns:
        the the platform unit as a String; may be null if not provided.

      • getKeySequence

        NucleotideSequence getKeySequence()
        Get the key sequence for each read group (454 and iontorrent only).
        Returns:
        the NucleotideSequence representing the keysequence or null if the keysequence is not specified or is not used by this read group.

      • getFlowOrder

        NucleotideSequence getFlowOrder()
        Get the flow order for each read group (454 and iontorrent only).
        Returns:
        the NucleotideSequence representing the floworder or null if the floworder is not specified or is not used by this read group.

      • getSequencingCenter

        String getSequencingCenter()
        Get the sequencingCenter that produced this read group.
        Returns:
